1
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,680
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

2
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:50,240
REFORM FOR GROWTH

3
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:03,880
DRIVE SLOWLY, SAFETY FIRST

4
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:20,000
Sir. Busy? Have a drink.

5
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,040
No, thanks.

6
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:24,880
Anyway,

7
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:27,160
did the owner of the factory come today?

8
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,560
Which owner?

9
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,400
Mr. Song Qingsong.

10
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,680
I don't know about that,
but you can't park your car there.

11
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:35,280
If you're not here to get it fixed,
move it away.

12
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,280
Understood?

13
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:37,960
Get it fixed.

14
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:39,040
I'm here to get it fixed.

15
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:41,680
Look how damaged it is.
Check it and quote a price.

16
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,440
You parked at a great spot.

17
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:51,240
Your car is seriously damaged.

18
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:53,080
Did the other person run away?

19
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,800
Stop staring.

20
00:02:57,880 --> 00:02:59,280
You won't see Song here.

21
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:00,800
Why is that?

22
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:03,760
Those who can see Song
won't come to me and ask about him.

23
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:07,800
But isn't it weird?

24
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,640
The place is locked up tight.

25
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:13,160
And the guard is strong.

26
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:15,400
One might even say
he's guarding an armory.

27
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,480
Have you not heard?

28
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,360
There was a gang fight here two days ago.

29
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:19,800
More than 200 men.

30
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,400
It was huge.

31
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:23,040
I lost some of my wrenches.

32
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,400
A gang fight? With whom?

33
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,640
Cripple Du.

34
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,680
Song's rival.

35
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,800
But why?

36
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,560
For business. The business in the mine.

37
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,720
The mine?

38
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,800
Dongshan Mine?

39
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,920
Do you see another mine in Weiyang?

40
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:44,200
It's run by the government.
Very lucrative.

41
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,520
QINGSONG CEMENT

42
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:19,800
PATTIA FRONT DESK

43
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,279
Uncle Ran,

44
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,640
now that we have checked
the underground labyrinth,

45
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,080
it's time to check the labyrinth upstairs.

46
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,920
We need to change our method for that.

47
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,960
Change our method?

48
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,960
We'll use Tremeaux's algorithm.

49
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:33,240
Tremor? Like land tremors?

50
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,040
Here.

51
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:39,000
Trémaux's algorithm
is the most time-intensive

52
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:42,400
yet the most likely to succeed
among all labyrinth solvers.

53
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:45,680
In short, take every route

54
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:48,320
and mark them so that we don't make
the same mistake.

55
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:51,000
In the end, we'll find the exit.

56
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:53,880
To translate it
into our investigation, it means

57
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:54,920
we have to first find a lead.

58
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:58,320
Uncle Ran, you make it sound
too complicated.

59
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,400
Forget about tremors. Just do this.

60
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,760
This is the entrance. This is the exit.

61
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,160
Now, you'll find the solution.

62
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,680
Give it back.

63
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,320
WEIYANG CITY DONGSHAN
MINE OPERATION CONTRACTOR TENDER DOCUMENT

64
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,440
Come in.

65
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,600
Mr. Song.

66
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,640
Hear me out.

67
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,760
Yesterday, I…

68
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,160
You did well last night.

69
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,520
You're smart.

70
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,040
This is your reward.

71
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,160
Mr. Song, I was just doing my job.

72
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,360
So, take it.

73
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,480
I…

74
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,280
Thank you.

75
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:02,480
When will you return the things
worth hundreds of thousands of yuan

76
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,960
stolen from Yuanlongli?

77
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,560
Immediately.

78
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,280
Immediately.

79
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,880
Where did you bury the woman?

80
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,240
After I was released yesterday,
the police have been following me.

81
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,840
I'll dig out the body now.

82
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:16,960
Did I tell you to do that?

83
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,400
Are you dumb?

84
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,200
Then, I won't dig the body out. I…

85
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:22,720
Burn it. Destroy it.

86
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,160
Dissolve it. Deal with it.

87
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,280
Okay.

88
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,680
Take a picture before you get rid of it.

89
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,800
Okay.

90
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,440
AUTO MAINTENANCE, REPAIR SHOP

91
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:48,680
Mr. Song.

92
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,320
The officer from yesterday
is still waiting outside.

93
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,960
What if he follows me?

94
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:55,320
You made a mess and you expect me
to clean up after you?

95
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:05,200
If you fail to handle this properly
and the police find out,

96
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:06,520
you'll turn yourself in.

97
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,040
Otherwise,

98
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,200
I'll make your family disappear.

99
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,880
Let's see how long you can stay in there.

100
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,600
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

101
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,960
I'M BRINGING XIAOHE TO YUANLONGLI. RAN

102
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,360
Yuanlongli?

103
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:43,560
Why that place of all places?

104
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:46,240
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

105
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,200
Stop!

106
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,560
XINFENG AUTO REPAIR

107
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,960
Who told you to do this? You jerk!

108
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,440
Asshole!

109
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:18,800
Hey! Hey!

110
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,440
Song Qingsong, you son of…

111
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,920
Careful, Xiaohe.

112
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,440
Xiaohe.

113
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,440
Slow down.

114
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:43,080
Red, orange, yellow, green,

115
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,280
green, blue, purple.

116
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,680
Everyone is here.

117
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,880
Big butt!

118
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,760
- Big butt!
- What are you doing?

119
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,240
Let go!

120
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,600
Let go!

121
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,160
Rat! Pickpocket! Money-grubber!

122
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:36,480
How come everywhere we go,
we always see you?

123
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,160
It's you again?

124
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:40,920
Mr. Qian. She is asking your question.

125
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,440
Officer Ran,

126
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:46,920
someone complained about a stench.

127
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,320
So, I came up here to check.

128
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:52,600
I thought someone
must have planted something.

129
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:55,080
Who knew that someone
was raising chickens here?

130
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:56,200
Unbelievable.

131
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,760
Why did you enter the chicken coop then?

132
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,520
To count the chickens.

133
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,800
How can I fine them without knowing
how many chickens are here?

134
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,480
I'll get someone from the management here.

135
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:08,800
This is unbelievable.

136
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,080
Unbelievable! I must clean it!

137
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,480
The chicken coop needs to be removed.

138
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,520
Qian!

139
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:19,440
- How dare you!
- Sir.

140
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:21,000
Sir.

141
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:23,600
What are you doing?

142
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:26,760
Qian Dajun.

143
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,680
Calm down.

144
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,280
Let me make myself clear today.

145
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:32,160
Touch my chickens
and I'll chop off your hands.

146
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,120
Sir. Calm down.

147
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,520
There's an officer here.

148
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,920
- Calm down.
- I don't care!

149
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,600
- Calm down. Calm down.
- Stay right there.

150
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,560
- Stay right there.
- Calm down.

151
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,320
Calm down.

152
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,600
- That jerk.
- Calm down.

153
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:51,400
Mister, you're amazing.

154
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:54,240
Did you raise all these colorful chickens?

155
00:10:57,040 --> 00:11:00,120
Yes. Little girl, do you like them?

156
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:03,000
If you like them, I can give you one.

157
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,600
Thanks, mister.

158
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:12,200
Forget about it.
My mother won't let me raise it.

159
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,280
Give me a moment.

160
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:37,040
Thank you, mister.

161
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:41,320
I wonder what color this chick will be.

162
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,320
Hey!

163
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,400
It's a raw egg!

164
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:11,080
DANFENG MIDDLE SCHOOL

165
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:13,120
PRINCIPAL'S ROOM

166
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,120
Officer He, this is the place.

167
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,080
Thank you.

168
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,160
You're welcome.

169
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,480
Come in.

170
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,960
Hello, Principal Qin. I am He Xiaohe.

171
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:28,880
I'm here for Han Zi'ang.

172
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,840
Oh.

173
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,480
Officer He. Take a seat.

174
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,680
Thank you.

175
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:40,240
Principal Qin, I know you're a busy man,
so I'll keep it brief.

176
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:44,560
I came to urge you
to reconsider the decision

177
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,720
to expel Han Zi'ang.

178
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,760
Officer He.

179
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:51,240
I already explained to you clearly

180
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,440
in our phone call yesterday.

181
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:59,080
It's a decision that we made
upon deliberate consideration.

182
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,280
But…

183
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,840
Please let me finish.

184
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:05,720
The expulsion isn't my decision.

185
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:09,920
In class, Han Zi'ang dozes off often.

186
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,480
And he often misses classes
for no reason at all.

187
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:15,200
This time, instead of truancy,

188
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:18,240
he stabbed someone outside.

189
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:21,680
Principal Qin, does Han Zi'ang
have a history of violence?

190
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,360
Not that I know of.

191
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:29,360
His homeroom teacher told us
that he was usually quiet.

192
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:34,360
But you know, the quiet one
turns out to be the most volatile.

193
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,680
This is just a stereotype.

194
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:39,480
From what I was told,
Han Zi'ang is indeed an introvert.

195
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:41,240
But that's because he likes to read.

196
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:44,600
Of course, what he reads are comic books.

197
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:48,720
Perhaps he mixed
fictional elements with reality.

198
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:51,720
When he heard that Yuanlongli was haunted,

199
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,760
he went on an adventure.

200
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,360
He ran into a homeless guy,

201
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:59,080
and then maybe, he was anxious and scared.

202
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,960
So, he stabbed him to defend himself.

203
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:08,600
Officer He, you're saying
that Han Zi'ang acted out of self-defense.

204
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:10,120
I get that.

205
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:13,040
But the parents don't get that.

206
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,360
He stabbed someone.

207
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,640
That's the truth.

208
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,760
If he comes to school,

209
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,640
the other parents will be worried sick.

210
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:27,800
He is still unconscious in the hospital.

211
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:31,200
The police are doing their best
to investigate the case.

212
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:33,400
Before the truth comes out,

213
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:36,320
I urge the school not to give up on him.

214
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,600
If someone lends him a hand
at a time like this,

215
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,200
you're not just saving his education,

216
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:44,640
you're saving his life.

217
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,440
Principal Qin.

218
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:49,160
In fact,

219
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:53,360
I was worse and more rebellious
than he was back then.

220
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:57,960
But someone in my life
never gave up on me.

221
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:03,240
He pulled me back in time
and saved my life.

222
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:05,960
That's why I can be
an officer like I am now.

223
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:10,120
Principal Qin, for a child,

224
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:14,480
one decision can determine his whole life.

225
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:18,320
I urge you to reconsider.

226
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:23,400
Perhaps you can be the one
who saves Han Zi'ang.

227
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,960
Officer He, how about this?

228
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,960
Since Han Zi'ang is still unconscious,

229
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:36,200
we'll delay his expulsion
as much as possible.

230
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,440
Before the investigation comes to an end,

231
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,360
I can speak on behalf of the school

232
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:44,320
that if the police
provide proof that Han Zi'ang

233
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:47,800
acted out of self-defense,

234
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:50,360
then we can reconsider the expulsion.

235
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:52,760
Okay.

236
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:53,720
Thank you.

237
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,520
Thank you, Principal Qin.

238
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:10,080
Even at this age, Xiaohe is still a rebel.

239
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:13,720
She just swallows whatever hardships.

240
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:17,560
Sir, Xiaohe is almost like my junior.

241
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:19,480
She studied for six years
to be a criminal police officer.

242
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:20,640
Have faith in her.

243
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:23,400
She's my daughter.
Of course, I have faith in her.

244
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:25,360
I'm her dad, after all.

245
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:28,760
She also grew up under your nose.

246
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,800
But this is her first case.

247
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:33,120
She needs all the support she can have.

248
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,280
It was my first case back then too.

249
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:39,360
But you didn't pamper me.

250
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,240
Nonsense!

251
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,320
Did you acknowledge me
as your mentor back then?

252
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:49,120
The older you are,
the more grudges you hold.

253
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,960
NOTICE, YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL
GARDEN REDEVELOPMENT MEETING

254
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,160
THE MEETING WILL BE HELD AT 1 P.M. TODAY.

255
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,599
Why did they seal it off?

256
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:20,280
That side wasn't involved.
Why seal that place?

257
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:21,560
Let's go, sir.

258
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,800
SEALED, NANSHAN BRANCH
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU

259
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,240
I don't think we'll find anything here.

260
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,520
Should we go to the surveillance room?

261
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,800
Sir.

262
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:34,480
The surveillance room
was demolished a long time ago.

263
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:35,480
You already know about that.

264
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:37,600
Oh.

265
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,160
Then, let's head
to the underground car park.

266
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:42,120
I bet you have no idea

267
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,920
what it has become after all these years.

268
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,320
Sir, let's leave.

269
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,920
Just stay out of the case.

270
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,760
If this turns out to be a prank…

271
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:53,600
Eighteen years ago,
they also said the Xu Meng case

272
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:54,800
was a prank.

273
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,240
What did you do?

274
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,720
Sir, just tell the truth.

275
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,880
You want to keep me here in Weiyang

276
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,280
to investigate the case 18 years ago.

277
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,600
Qiao lives in Yuanlongli.

278
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,280
Don't you want to see her?

279
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:40,880
Officer Ran.

280
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:42,880
Qiao.

281
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:45,000
Sorry to disturb you again.

282
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:48,680
And this is…

283
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:51,280
Hi, miss. I am He Xiaohe.

284
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,360
My father is He Yuanhang.

285
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,480
He works with Uncle Ran.

286
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:58,560
Hi, Xiaohe. I am Qiao Suqing.

287
00:18:58,640 --> 00:18:59,560
It's nice to meet you.

288
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,720
Miss, you're so pretty.

289
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:07,240
No wonder Uncle Ran
brought me here specifically.

290
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,200
Come. Come in.

291
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,680
Change your shoes.

292
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,200
Xiaohe.

293
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,880
What do you want to drink?

294
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,440
- This one.
- This one?

295
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:46,880
Then, Officer Ran…

296
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:48,520
Thank you.

297
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,400
- Here.
- Thank you.

298
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:58,640
Miss, your house is so clean.

299
00:19:58,720 --> 00:19:59,640
And it smells good too.

300
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,760
Thank you, Xiaohe.

301
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:02,920
I'm living alone.

302
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,320
When I'm free, I like to clean my house.

303
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,160
You're living alone?

304
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,640
Do you have a boyfriend?

305
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:12,680
No.

306
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:15,120
From what I know,

307
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:18,000
Uncle Ran doesn't have
a girlfriend either.

308
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,800
Don't get me wrong.

309
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:28,200
I'm just telling facts.

310
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:37,880
Xiaohe.

311
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:39,400
Go take a shower here.

312
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:40,760
I'll come back later
to pick you up. All right?

313
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,440
No. I have to explore the maze with you.

314
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:44,600
You must stay here.

315
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:46,160
Look at you now.

316
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,880
When your father comes here,
how am I supposed to hand you back to him?

317
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,120
Come.

318
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:54,840
Xiaohe. Let's get you
all cleaned up, okay?

319
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:57,360
Officer Ran, don't let me keep you.

320
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:58,920
I'll take care of Xiaohe.

321
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,080
Don't worry.

322
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:02,160
Thank you.

323
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,800
Uncle Ran, you're blushing.

324
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,240
Am I?

325
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:11,120
Let's go to the shower.

326
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,880
Officer He.

327
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:30,080
What happened to you?

328
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:31,520
Is the case almost over?

329
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:34,440
I'm waiting for my tip-off reward.

330
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:36,360
So am I.

331
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:40,240
Please supervise the young one well.

332
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:43,320
Don't let him
get carried away by his needs.

333
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:44,720
Young one? Who?

334
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:45,960
Officer Ran.

335
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:49,640
I keep seeing him visiting Unit 415.

336
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:51,800
A mistress lives there.

337
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:53,600
Don't make things up.

338
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:54,840
I didn't.

339
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:57,320
I just saw him take a little girl

340
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,440
to the mistress's home.

341
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:08,120
Du, if you are bored,

342
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:11,760
study how the amazing detectives
solve the cases in your detective novels.

343
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:14,280
Don't just stare at your neighbors
and spread rumors.

344
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:15,640
But I…

345
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,520
You told me

346
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,720
to give you useful information,
didn't you?

347
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:22,760
I can't believe it.

348
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:26,800
Come. Eat while it's warm.

349
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:27,840
Wow!

350
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:29,760
Ms. Qiao.

351
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:33,800
You're just like a real-life super nanny.

352
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:36,160
You're a smooth-talker.

353
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,200
Dig in.

354
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,560
What's the matter?

355
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:48,720
It'd be great if I could call you
auntie in the future.

356
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:51,640
Witty, aren't you?

357
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:55,200
I've never thought
of Officer Ran that way.

358
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:56,920
You're lying.

359
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,040
I'm telling the truth.

360
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:01,720
I was just saying
I'd like to call you auntie.

361
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:04,400
Why did you think of Uncle Ran right away?

362
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,240
How dare you!

363
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:10,920
Coming.

364
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:15,800
You can't wait to see him.

365
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:22,160
You're…

366
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:23,120
Dad!

367
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:25,880
Xiaohe.

368
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,640
Officer He. Come in.

369
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,600
It's okay. I'm all dusty.

370
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:32,400
- I'm here to pick my kid up.
- It's okay.

371
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:34,560
Dad, I went inside
a chicken coop just now.

372
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:36,280
Did you go inside a pigsty or something?

373
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:38,960
I didn't get into a pigsty,
but I was harassed by pigs.

374
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:41,360
Officer He. Please come in.

375
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,440
Let me get you a fresh towel.

376
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:44,480
Sorry about that.

377
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:51,600
You even took a shower. Where's Uncle Ran?

378
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:54,600
He's solving the maze on the 18th floor.

379
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:57,200
Ms. Qiao's shampoo smells so good.

380
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:58,640
Her egg noodles are delicious too.

381
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:02,120
Dad, you must thank her
for taking good care of me.

382
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,200
Here, Officer He. Clean yourself.

383
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:07,240
Sure. Thank you.

384
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:09,000
My daughter must have troubled you a lot.

385
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:11,640
Not at all. She's so obedient.

386
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:13,480
Officer He, do stay here.

387
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:16,520
It's okay. I'll just wipe myself quickly.

388
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:21,800
Dad, I love Ms. Qiao.

389
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,920
Can Uncle Ran bring me here often?

390
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:30,960
Go. Wash the towel for Ms. Qiao.

391
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:50,280
Thank you.

392
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,240
Officer He,

393
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:59,200
I know I have a bad reputation

394
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:02,640
and that I should stay away
from Officer Ran.

395
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:10,200
But I am not what they say I am.

396
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:17,160
I only trust what I see with my own eyes.

397
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:20,240
Don't take those rumors to heart.

398
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,720
If you have done nothing wrong,

399
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:26,040
there's no need
to worry about false rumors.

400
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:40,520
COME TO THE OPPOSITE
OF THE FOOT MASSAGE PARLOR QUICKLY, LILI

401
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,960
Do you have to make a call?

402
00:25:47,040 --> 00:25:48,360
You can use my line.

403
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:50,080
It's okay.

404
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:54,120
Can I trouble you
to look after Xiaohe for a while?

405
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:55,680
I might have to pick her up later.

406
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:56,960
Sure. No trouble at all.

407
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:59,800
I couldn't be happier that Xiaohe is here.

408
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:02,160
Me too.

409
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:04,240
Look at her.

410
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:05,360
Be a good girl.

411
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,880
Thank you so much.

412
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:17,440
FLEA MARKET

413
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:40,560
THE USUAL PLACE TONIGHT AT EIGHT
SEE YOU

414
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,120
What do you want?

415
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,920
Look at the car plate.

416
00:26:57,440 --> 00:27:00,280
I am the deputy manager
at Qingsong Cement Factory.

417
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:03,720
Thugs like you best not touch me.

418
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,320
- I'm looking for you, you punk.
- For what?

419
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:12,640
A guy of mine, Wolfie,

420
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:14,480
was arrested by the police two days ago.

421
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:16,160
Do you know what happened?

422
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:17,080
No idea.

423
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:20,880
Do you know or not?

424
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:23,080
Yes. I know.

425
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:26,520
I know.

426
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:29,320
Your guy didn't kill anyone.

427
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,640
Don't tell me everything.

428
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:34,200
Just answer my question.

429
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:35,840
Okay.

430
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:39,120
Did Song Qingsong make the offer?

431
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:41,040
No.

432
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:42,080
I did.

433
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:44,720
I can swear on my life. I made the offer.

434
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:46,560
I'm trying to become clean, you know?

435
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,400
Since you made the offer,

436
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:51,400
pay up.

437
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:53,240
Pay what?

438
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:55,360
Your guy didn't even finish the job.

439
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:56,800
Why should I pay up?

440
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:59,600
Why? Why?

441
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:02,960
Did I tell you to do that?

442
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:05,040
Let's just be civil.

443
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:06,280
Be professional.

444
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:13,240
My guy is an important person
in the company.

445
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:17,520
And because of you, he was arrested
and is still not yet released.

446
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:21,000
Should we calculate the loss of profit?

447
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:22,600
The loss of profit?

448
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,240
Your guy didn't finish the job.

449
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:29,000
I had to clean up after him
and deal with those two.

450
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:31,640
You killed them?

451
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:33,680
Right.

452
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,280
I didn't know you were this ruthless.

453
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,880
One slash, one life.

454
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:42,280
Not bad.

455
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:44,600
What about my loss of profit?

456
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:49,760
That's easy.

457
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:54,120
We won't extort each other.

458
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,760
Aren't you the second in command
of the cement factory?

459
00:28:58,120 --> 00:28:59,200
That's an important position.

460
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:03,600
Sign a contractor agreement with me
worth 300,000 yuan.

461
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:04,600
You're the client.

462
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:05,560
I'm the contractor.

463
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,000
Good enough?

464
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,880
Maybe we can just settle
the balance instead.

465
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:16,480
- Will you sign it or not?
- Yes!

466
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:18,040
Yes. Yes.

467
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:28,120
I like how decisive you are, Mr. Wu.

468
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:35,920
CONTRACTOR AGREEMENT

469
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,320
CLIENT: WU SHANLONG
CONTRACTOR: JIN MANSHAN

470
00:29:40,360 --> 00:29:42,920
Tell them to tell Manlang.

471
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:44,280
Okay.

472
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:48,640
Speak.

473
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:52,960
Ms. Zhao forbids us
from mentioning Mengmeng.

474
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:55,680
My friends and I only gossip in secret.

475
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:58,760
They think a client is suspicious.

476
00:30:00,320 --> 00:30:01,120
Who?

477
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:04,640
When he came, he only asked for Mengmeng.

478
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,480
And he paid double.

479
00:30:06,560 --> 00:30:08,080
We call him Mr. Sun.

480
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:09,240
Mr. Sun?

481
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:12,760
He was already a regular at Pattia.

482
00:30:12,840 --> 00:30:15,720
And he always came with a bag
of branded clothes.

483
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:18,120
The brands inside were so expensive.

484
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,880
Branded clothes.

485
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:23,400
Double Fish.

486
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:25,160
It's expensive.

487
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:27,480
Bowls.

488
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:31,360
This dress is probably
worth more than this unit.

489
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:38,360
Did Mr. Sun hand out goods
from Bowls and Double Fish?

490
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:42,040
Bowls and Double Fish…

491
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,200
I can't remember.

492
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:48,880
What is Mr. Sun's real name?

493
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:50,800
I'm not sure.

494
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:56,640
But after Mengmeng went missing,
Mr. Sun stopped showing up.

495
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:07,600
Sir, I've told you what I know.

496
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:10,240
I hope you can find Mengmeng soon.

497
00:31:10,320 --> 00:31:11,800
I'm quite worried about her.

498
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:15,200
Don't worry. We've been searching for her.

499
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:16,600
Your information is very important.

500
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,360
Thank you, Lili.

501
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:21,400
If there's nothing else, I have to go now.

502
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:24,520
A HOME VISIT TO XU MENG’S UNCLE,
QIAO GUOQIANG.

503
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,360
CLEAR MARKS ON THE FLOOR
BY THE FOOT OF THE BED,

504
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:26,160
INDICATING IT HAS BEEN MOVED.

505
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:29,720
Oh.

506
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:32,480
When I was at Pattia,
a woman called Zhizhi

507
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:34,400
was quite close to Mr. Sun.

508
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:36,120
You can look for her.

509
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,040
Zhizhi.

510
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,040
Su Yuzhi.

511
00:31:49,280 --> 00:31:50,880
A rich guy? What's his name?

512
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,880
Sun, I think.

513
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:54,160
His name?

514
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:56,360
I don't know.

515
00:32:00,360 --> 00:32:01,960
She lied.

516
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,600
Adult Gaokao…

517
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:34,440
I thought only students sit for exams.

518
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:36,920
Adults have to do it too?

519
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:39,360
It's adult gaokao.

520
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:42,040
It's a chance for people like me
who never went to high school

521
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:43,840
to enter a university.

522
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,960
Oh. You want to impress Uncle Ran.

523
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:50,120
You're teasing me again.

524
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:54,640
Officer Ran is an ace student
from a prestigious school.

525
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:59,640
I started working after junior high.

526
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,040
So, I could only perform

527
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:06,280
physical labor,
like taking care of someone.

528
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:09,520
That's why I want to study hard,

529
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:12,800
get a degree, and find a good job.

530
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:16,200
- You can do this.
- Why do you say so?

531
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:18,920
Because you are the hardworking Ms. Qiao.

532
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:23,320
My mom told me that hard work
could make your dreams come true.

533
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:26,000
Your mom is right.

534
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:32,320
I, too, have to study hard.

535
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:39,240
- Do you even understand it?
- That's why I have to study.

536
00:33:39,320 --> 00:33:42,520
I want to be an ace student
like Uncle Ran.

537
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:45,560
Then, let's have a pinky promise.

538
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:48,120
We will both
be ace students in the future.

539
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,320
Sure.

540
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:52,120
You make a pinky promise,

541
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:54,200
you keep it all your life.

542
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:04,480
YUZHI BOUTIQUE

543
00:34:15,639 --> 00:34:18,320
The latest collection.
Pick anything you like.

544
00:34:28,199 --> 00:34:29,239
Excuse me.

545
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:36,880
Cutie. You're finally here.

546
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,600
Are you here to treat me to hotpot?

547
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,520
No.

548
00:34:41,199 --> 00:34:44,080
I'm here to ask you about Mr. Sun.

549
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:46,360
You said you weren't
close to him last time.

550
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:47,400
You lied.

551
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:52,120
Without lying, how else
could I make you come to me?

552
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:55,440
It's a game of flirting.

553
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:57,200
Su Yuzhi.

554
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:58,880
I brought him here.

555
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:01,160
So, tell us the truth now.

556
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:04,240
Cutie, what truth do you want to hear?

557
00:35:07,600 --> 00:35:09,960
Please tell me who Mr. Sun is.

558
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:15,440
Sun's name is Sun Zhengyong.

559
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:16,640
He's from Fujian.

560
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:19,240
He has shares in my boutique, too.

561
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:20,720
Don't get the wrong idea.

562
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:22,720
We are not intimate.

563
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:24,880
What about him and Xu Meng?

564
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:29,400
If I tell you,

565
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:31,240
will you still come to me in the future?

566
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:35,680
Please… Please answer my question.

567
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:43,080
Did Sun Zhengyong give this dress to you?

568
00:35:43,160 --> 00:35:44,640
Mind your tongue now.

569
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:50,600
I bought it from him. Wholesale.

570
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:55,800
FASHION BOUTIQUE

571
00:35:57,560 --> 00:35:59,560
This is… A counterfeit?

572
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:02,040
Counterfeits sell like hot cakes.

573
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:05,080
So, Sun Zhengyong
bought the authentic products,

574
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:07,080
then made counterfeits
to sell them in wholesale.

575
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,200
Cutie, you're smart.

576
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:11,680
You figured it out.

577
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:18,000
How does he deal
with the authentic products?

578
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:21,880
Normally, he gives them to girls he likes.

579
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:24,520
He gives them to Xu Meng?

580
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:25,840
I guess so.

581
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:27,280
He likes Mengmeng the most.

582
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:30,720
Are you saying Mr. Sun has something to do
with Mengmeng's disappearance?

583
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:32,440
What do you think?

584
00:36:33,640 --> 00:36:34,800
I don't know.

585
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:39,560
I saw them argue once.

586
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:41,400
When was it? And where?

587
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:43,200
At Pattia.

588
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:44,800
Mr. Sun was drunk.

589
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:48,000
He hugged Mengmeng
and asked her to be his girlfriend.

590
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:50,800
Mengmeng said no,
and Mr. Sun lost his patience.

591
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:53,040
He said Mengmeng played hard to get
and looked down on him.

592
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:54,480
They then argued.

593
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,440
- And then?
- And then?

594
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:04,360
You raided Pattia.

595
00:37:09,120 --> 00:37:12,600
Is there any place in Weiyang
that sells authentic Bowls dresses?

596
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,880
It's a huge brand.

597
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:16,760
There's one official store in Weiyang.

598
00:37:16,840 --> 00:37:18,280
Right inside Weiyang Mall.

599
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:21,680
Can you give us the wholesale address
of Sun Zhengyong?

600
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,000
NANMEN WHOLESALE MARKET
NANSHAN DISTRICT, WEIYANG CITY

601
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:33,920
FASHION CLOTHING HALL

602
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,120
Oh.

603
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:43,360
Remember the surprise I promised you?

604
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:46,560
We have a rule. We can't…

605
00:37:47,080 --> 00:37:48,600
I know.

606
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:51,040
I'll charge you the original price.

607
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,160
Five yuan.

608
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:58,160
Take it.

609
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:01,480
If you don't buy it,
she's going to lure you in again.

610
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:12,440
Thank you, Su Yuzhi.

611
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:14,760
I wish you a prosperous business.

612
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:21,800
See you.

613
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,120
Why not put it on now?

614
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:36,680
He.

615
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:39,960
I think Su Yuzhi
is telling the truth this time.

616
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:41,840
Of course.

617
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:43,680
She is so devoted to you.

618
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:44,600
He.

619
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:46,520
We're investigating a case. Be serious.

620
00:38:47,720 --> 00:38:48,800
Sure.

621
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:51,120
Then, analyze this seriously.

622
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:54,800
Perhaps Sun Zhengyong
thought Xu Meng looked down on him.

623
00:38:55,920 --> 00:38:58,560
His love turned into hatred,
and he killed her.

624
00:39:05,560 --> 00:39:06,920
YONG'S FASHION

625
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:08,840
Let me meet him in his shop.

626
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:12,240
I'll visit the official Bowls store
to check when he purchased the dress.

627
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:14,440
Not bad.

628
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:16,040
You've learned how to narrow down
the scope from me.

629
00:39:16,640 --> 00:39:17,840
That's progress.

630
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:23,680
Also, we shouldn't give up
on the lead on Song Qingsong.

631
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:25,640
Be patient. One at a time.

632
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:05,320
What happened to your head?

633
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:08,280
What could be so serious
that you couldn't say it on the phone?

634
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:11,120
What else could it be?

635
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:13,160
If it's about Song, forget it.

636
00:40:15,200 --> 00:40:16,360
Forget it?

637
00:40:17,160 --> 00:40:19,720
Wu Shanlong. Are you taking me for a fool?

638
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:21,600
Two plans.

639
00:40:21,680 --> 00:40:23,280
And both times,
you told me they were foolproof.

640
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:24,640
Then, what happened?

641
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:29,560
You're putting it as if it were my fault.

642
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:31,280
You came to me first,

643
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:33,760
saying that we could work together
to scam money out of Song.

644
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:37,400
I don't care about his money anymore.

645
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:42,240
Can you even hear what you just said?

646
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:45,120
The police are after Mengmeng.

647
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:47,840
Song Qingsong wants me to turn myself in.

648
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:55,840
So, if you turn yourself in
and they interrogate you,

649
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:57,840
will you rat me out?

650
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:05,720
I knew it.

651
00:41:05,800 --> 00:41:09,280
If men were reliable, pigs could fly.

652
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:12,720
I was forced to.

653
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:14,400
Do you have a plan or not?

654
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:16,680
Didn't you just say my plan was useless?

655
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:17,640
Zhao Hongmei,

656
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:19,800
let me remind you
that we're both in the same boat.

657
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:25,800
We're past the point of no return.

658
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:27,880
We can't do this forever.

659
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:30,200
Wu Shanlong.

660
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:34,320
I want you to tell me the truth.

661
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:36,200
Otherwise, forget everything.

662
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:37,920
Mengmeng.

663
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:42,040
Is she dead or alive?

664
00:41:44,080 --> 00:41:45,280
She's dead.

665
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:47,800
Stone cold dead!

666
00:41:50,560 --> 00:41:52,360
For goodness's sake.
